==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: blindside
<hw>blindside</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to attack a
person from his <cref>blind side</cref>; metaphorically, to give a
person an unpleasant surprise.</def> <illu>He had completed his plan to
develop a new office building, but was <ex>blindsided</ex> by the sudden
drop in real estate values.</illu>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

